Stimfit Debian maintenance workflow (CMake toolchain)
=====================================================

Branch model
------------

- Upstream code branch (current CMake transition): `pr/msvc-toolchain-compat`
- Debian packaging branch: `debian/sid`
- Pristine tar branch: `pristine-tar`

Once CMake lands on `master`, switch the upstream branch reference back to
`master` in `.gbp.conf` and continue the same workflow.

`gbp` defaults are configured in `.gbp.conf`.


Typical maintainer flow
-----------------------

1) Sync packaging branch with upstream:

   - Merge or rebase `pr/msvc-toolchain-compat` into `debian/sid`.

2) Build source + binary packages with git-buildpackage:

   - `gbp buildpackage --git-pristine-tar --git-builder=sbuild`

3) Optional local cowbuilder flow (legacy helper):

   - `debian/mkdeb.sh --force`

4) Run lintian on resulting `.changes`:

   - `lintian ../*.changes`

5) Run autopkgtest against produced binaries:

   - `autopkgtest ../*.changes -- null`
   - or with a VM backend if available.


Build system notes
------------------

- Debian rules now use `dh` with `cmake+ninja`.
- Debian-specific build flags are enabled via `-DSTF_BUILD_DEBIAN=ON`.
- Hardening remains controlled by `DEB_BUILD_MAINT_OPTIONS=hardening=+all`.


Release choreography
--------------------

1) Finalize `debian/changelog` entry.
2) Build and validate (sbuild + lintian + autopkgtest).
3) Tag upstream version as `upstream/<version>`.
4) Tag Debian upload as `debian/<version>`.
5) Upload signed `.changes`.
